*[[Lagos Lagoon]] in Lagos, Nigeria
*[[Lake Pontchartrain]], [[New Orleans, Louisiana|New Orleans]], [[Louisiana]], [[United States|U.S.]]
*[[Pulicat Lake]], north of [[Chennai]], [[India]]
*The [[Rann of Kutch]], on the border of [[India]] and [[Pakistan]]
*Parts of the [[Rhône River|Rhône]] Delta, [[France]]: An area known as the [[Camargue]]
*[[Widewater]], and [[land-locked]] [[lagoon]] near [[Lancing, West Sussex|Lancing]], [[England]]

'''Estuaries'''
*[[Amazon River]], empties so much freshwater into the [[Atlantic Ocean]] that it reduces the salinity of the sea for hundreds of miles
*[[Chesapeake Bay]], located in [[Maryland]] and [[Virginia]]. It is the drowned river valley of the [[Susquehanna River]]. It is the largest estuary in the United States.
*[[Delaware Bay]], an extension of the [[Delaware River]] in [[New Jersey]] and [[Delaware]], USA
*Lower [[Hudson River]], in [[New York]] and [[New Jersey]], [[United States|U.S.]]
*[[East River]] and [[Harlem River]], [[New York]], USA
*[[Lingding Yang]], [[Guangdong]], the [[People's Republic of China]]
*[[Port Royal Sound]] part of Beaufort County, [[South Carolina]], USA [http://www.lowcountryestuarium.org]
*[[Río de la Plata]], in [[Argentina]] and [[Uruguay]].&lt;ref name=seeliger&gt;{{cite book |last= Seeliger |first= Ulrich |last2= Kjerfve |first2= Björn |title= Coastal Marine Ecosystems of Latin America |year= 2001 |publisher= Springer |isbn= 9783540672289 |url= http://books.google.com/books?id=drF30PA45o8C&amp;pg=PA185 |pages= 185–204}}&lt;/ref&gt;
*[[Saint Lawrence River|Saint Lawrence]] and [[Saguenay River|Saguenay]] Rivers, the part downstream from [[Quebec City|Québec]] and [[Saguenay, Quebec|Saguenay]] respectively
*[[San Francisco Bay]] and [[San Pablo Bay]] adjacent to [[San Francisco]] in [[California]], [[U.S.]]
*The [[Thames Estuary]] in South East [[England]]

