The second half of the 20th century was marked by the rise of communal conflicts between the Flemings and the Francophones &lt;!--a quarter of the Francophones are living in Brussels and are not nessarily Walloons but are nevertheless in conflict with the Flemings, so please don't change Francophone into Walloons--&gt; fuelled by [[culture of Belgium|cultural differences]] on the one hand and an [[economy of Belgium|asymmetrical economic evolution]] of Flanders and Wallonia on the other hand. [[2007–2011 Belgian political crisis|These still-active conflicts]] have caused far-reaching [[state reform in Belgium|reforms of the formerly unitary Belgian state into a federal state]] which might lead to a [[partition of Belgium|partition of the country]].&lt;ref
 name=SanFranChro&gt;
